–1410","1390–1460":"1390.–1460","1350–Female":"1350.–preminula","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350.","1460":"1460","1371":"1371.","1390":"1390.","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, England","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1350–":"1350–Zesnulá","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Zesnulá","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, Anglie","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1350–":"1350–Afdød","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Afdød","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, England","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1350–":"1350–Overleden","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Overleden","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, England","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1350–":"1350–Deceased","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Deceased","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, England","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Stratton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: habitational name from any of several places called Stratton or Stretton, almost all named with Old English <i>strǣt</i> ‘paved road, Roman road’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’. Stratton in Cornwall, which may also be a partial source of the surname, probably has as its first element Cornish <i>stras</i> ‘valley’.","English: variant of <b>Sturton</b>, a habitational name from Sturton le Steeple (Nottinghamshire), Great Sturton (Lincolnshire), Sturton by Stow (Lincolnshire), or possibly Sturton (Northumberland), all of which placenames share the same etymology and early spellings as 1 above.","Scottish: habitational name from Straiton (Ayrshire), Straiton in Liberton (Midlothian), or South Straiton in Logie (Fife), all named with Old English <i>strǣt</i> ‘street, Roman road’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."],"variants":[{"name":"Stretton","meanings":["English (Leicestershire): variant of   Stratton   1."]},{"name":"Strutton","meanings":["English (Middlesex): variant of   Stratton  ."]},{"name":"Straiton","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Straiton (Ayrshire), Straiton in Liberton (Midlothian), or South Straiton in Logie (Fife), all named with Old English <i>strǣt</i> ‘paved road, street’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Stratton  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Stratton was born in 1350, in Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir John Gresham in 1371, in Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1350–":"1350–Surnud","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Surnud","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, England","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1350–":"1350–Kuollut","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Kuollut","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, England","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1350–":"1350–Décédée","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Décédée","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Stratton, Norfolk, Angleterre","Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Holt, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Gresham Manor, Holt, Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Stratton est née en 1350, à Holt, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Sir John Gresham en 1371, à Holt, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1350–":"1350–Verstorben","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1390–1460":"1390–1460","1350–Female":"1350–Verstorben","1348":"1348","1410":"1410","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1371":"1371","1390":"1390","Long Stratton, Norfolk, England":"Long Strat